<div class="dropdown">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="Faq">
        <span>What is JanManch?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <p>It’s a public platform where people can freely share their opinions on proposed laws, bills, and policies. We categorize responses into Agree, Disagree, or Neutral for better understanding of public sentiment.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="Faq">
        <span>Why should I share my opinion here?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <p>Your voice matters! By participating, you contribute to a collective record of how citizens feel about important legal decisions. This can help policymakers and researchers understand the pulse of the people.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="Faq">
        <span>Can I see the overall results?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <p>Yes! You can explore dashboards that show how many people agree, disagree, or remain neutral on each law.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="Faq">
        <span>How is this different from social media debates?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <p>Unlike noisy social platforms, JanManch is focused purely on structured opinions about laws. This makes discussions clearer, more organized, and easier to analyze.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="Faq">
        <span>Is my opinion anonymous?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <p>Yes. Your identity is safe with us. We only publish the opinion text and its classification, never your personal details.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="Faq">
        <span>Is it safe and unbiased?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <p>Absolutely. We do not modify or censor opinions (unless they contain hate speech/abuse). The categorization is fair and transparent.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        const faqs = document.querySelectorAll('.Faq');

        faqs.forEach(faqButton => {
            faqButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
                const answer = faqButton.nextElementSibling;

                faqButton.classList.toggle('active');
                answer.classList.toggle('open');
            });
        });
    });
</script>
  
